Discussion written to `discussion.md`. Four verdicts: Pass (lambda_1 > 0), Partial (spectrum within 20% -- lambda_2 misses), Pass (R^2 = 0.9997), Pass (LC monotonically improves closure). The main finding is that observation noise, not LC weight, is the dominant axis -- obs_noise=0 succeeds across all LC values while any noise collapses the learned dynamics. Hypothesis supported with the caveat that the near-zero exponent remains hard to recover.
